blocks.name: ifscgr
blocks.content: Inner five segment congruence. Take two triangles, ` A D C ` and ` E H G ` , with ` B ` between ` A ` and ` C ` and ` F ` between ` E ` and ` G ` . If the other components of the triangles are congruent, then so are ` B D ` and ` F H ` . Theorem 4.2 of [Schwabhauser] p. 34. (Contributed by Scott Fenton, 27-Sep-2013.)
